<plot>Musical show that was on in two different periods. It started as a summertime replacement show between June and August 1959, was brought back February to March 1960 for 30 minutes and then March to September 1960 for 60 minutes. The show consisted mainly of musical numbers from Broadway show tunes and the classics, e.g., "Madame Butterfly," "La Traviata," and "Tosca."</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?382381</url></doc>
